abstract: Iraqi authorities report car bomb explosions kill at least 26 people and injure 58; bombings occurred at congested markets in predominantly Shiite neighborhoods of Bayaa and Shaab in Baghdad, raising suspicions that Islamic State militants are responsible.
lead_paragraph: No one immediately claimed responsibility for the two attacks.
